main event: Observer watched six orange colored objects travel toward the horizon for 5-6 seconds.
interesting points: The objects were moving quite fast and were described as being highly maneuverable., The conclusion in the report suggested an explanation of 'Other (Circus)', The objects were noted to have a grayish orange color., An analyst was unable to determine a meaningful explanation for the sighting., The sighting involved a reliable and well-educated witness investigated by Rivers (Telescope).
witness description: Observer classified as reliable and well-educated
